'''Charles Newton Kimball''' (born February 20, 1985) is an American racecar driver currently competing in the [[IndyCar Series]] with [[Carlin Motorsport]]. He has scored a win, six podiums and 13 top 5s. His best season result was ninth in 2013 and 2016. In addition, he won the [[2013 24 Hours of Daytona]].

==Career==

===2002–2005===
Born in [[Chertsey]], England, Kimball's single-seater career started in 2002 when he took part in the American [[Barber Pro Series|Formula Dodge]] national championship, finishing the season in 10th place overall. He also won three races in the SCCA Formula Ford series. For 2003 he moved up to [[Formula Ford]] [[United States|US]], finishing third overall with two race wins and seven podium finishes. He also contested the [[United Kingdom|UK]] Formula Ford winter series, taking one race win to finish third overall.

In 2004, he competed in the full UK Formula Ford championship for ''Team JLR'', taking two race wins and eleven podiums on his way to fourth in the championship. In the end-of-season [[Formula Ford Festival]] at [[Brands Hatch]] he finished in eighth place. His performances earned him a drive with front runners [[Carlin Motorsport]] in the [[2005 British Formula 3 season|2005 British Formula 3 Championship]], where he took five race wins to finish an impressive second behind teammate [[Álvaro Parente]]. He also finished 12th in the [[Masters of Formula 3|Marlboro Masters]] at [[Circuit Park Zandvoort|Zandvoort]], but failed to finish the season-ending [[Macau Grand Prix]].

===2006–2008===
For 2006 Kimball stayed in [[Formula Three]], but moved up to the [[Formula 3 Euro Series]] with the [[France|French]] ''Signature-Plus'' team. He took one race win and three podiums to finish the season in eleventh place. Once again, he took part in the Masters Formula 3 race at Zandvoort and the Macau Grand Prix, finishing in 9th and 21st places respectively.

[[Image:Charlie Kimball 2007 WSBR.jpg|thumb|left|Kimball driving for [[Victory Engineering]] in the [[Donington Park]] round of the [[2007 Formula Renault 3.5 Series season]].]]
In 2007, he competed in the [[2007 Formula Renault 3.5 Series season|Formula Renault 3.5 Series]] for the [[Italy|Italian]] [[Victory Engineering]] team, alongside [[Netherlands|Dutchman]] [[Giedo van der Garde]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.crash.net/news_view~t~WS--Victory-completes-line-up-with-Kimball-~cid~7~id~141516.htm | title = Victory completes line-up with Kimball | publisher = crash.net | date = December 22, 2006 | accessdate = June 13, 2007 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070401121850/http://www.crash.net/news_view~t~WS--Victory-completes-line-up-with-Kimball-~cid~7~id~141516.htm | archivedate = April 1, 2007 | df = mdy-all }}</ref> He competed in 12 races (leaving the series with 2 race weekends remaining) and finished 24th in points with a best finish of 8th in the Monza and Nurburgring sprint races. His departed the team due to the onset of [[Diabetes mellitus type 1|Type 1 diabetes]] which required hospitalization. As part of his ongoing treatment he wears a wireless blood sugar monitor and carries sugar water on board the car while racing.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kelly|first=Peggy|url=http://www.santapaulatimes.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/15616/Charlie_Kimball:_Diabetes_doesn%92t_force_Formula_driver_off_the_road_to_fame.html|title=Charlie Kimball: Diabetes doesn't force Formula driver off the road to fame|work=Santa Paula Times|publisher=Debbie Johnson, Santa Paula Times|date=February 20, 2008|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref> In 2008, he returned to F3 EuroSeries for 6 races with [[Prema Powerteam]]. Late in 2008 he competed in the first round of the [[A1 Grand Prix]] series for [[A1 Team USA]].

===Firestone Indy Lights (2009–2010)===
For 2009 Kimball signed to drive in [[Indy Lights]] for the new [[Palm Beach International Raceway|Team PBIR]] outfit. He stated that an influencing factor in his return to the U.S. is to increase Diabetes awareness in his home country.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/motor/2009-03-24-3082157251_x.htm|title=Road racer signs with Indy Lights team|work=[[USA Today]]|publisher=[[Gannett Company]]|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=March 24, 2009|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref> Kimball finished 10th in points with a best finish of 4th at [[Watkins Glen International]].

He returned to in Indy Lights in 2010 and signed with [[AFS Racing]]/[[Andretti Autosport]]. Despite not winning a race or pole, Kimball had four second-place finishes on the season and captured 4th in points, one spot behind his teammate [[Martin Plowman]].

===IndyCar Series (2011–present)===
[[File:GoPro Grand Prix 2015 18 - Stierch.jpg|thumb|250px|Kimball driving the [[Novo Nordisk]] Ganassi car at the [[2015 GoPro Grand Prix of Sonoma]]]]
It was announced on December 16, 2010 that Kimball would move up to the [[IndyCar Series]] in [[2011 IndyCar Series season|2011]], in which he would drive the No. 83 entry for [[Chip Ganassi Racing]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/rpm/racing/indycar/columns/story?id=5926942|title=Rahal, Kimball join Ganassi team|work=[[ESPN.com]]|publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]]|first=John|last=Oreovicz|date=December 17, 2010|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref> Kimball finished 19th in points with a best finish of ninth at the [[New Hampshire Motor Speedway]]. Kimball returned to the team in 2012 and again finished 19th in points despite missing a race due to injury. He finished second at the [[Honda Indy Toronto]], his first career podium finish. In [[2013 24 Hours of Daytona|2013]], he competed in his first [[24 Hours of Daytona]] race with Ganassi and was on the race winning team with co-drivers [[Juan Pablo Montoya]], [[Scott Pruett]], and [[Memo Rojas]]. Kimball also won his first IndyCar race on August 4, 2013 at the [[2013 Honda Indy 200 at Mid-Ohio|Honda Indy 200 at Mid-Ohio]].

==Personal==
Kimball was born in England but grew up in [[Camarillo, California]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailybreeze.com/technology/20100413/charlie-kimball-aims-to-win-indy-500-despite-type-1-diabetes-diagnosis|title=Charlie Kimball aims to win Indy 500 despite Type 1 diabetes diagnosis|work=[[Daily Breeze]]|publisher=Ron Hasse, [[Digital First Media]]|first=David|last=Felton|date=April 13, 2010|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref> His father Gordon was a designer of [[Formula One]] and Indy cars.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.racer.com/indycar/item/112888-indycar-2018-by-gordon-kimball|title=IndyCar 2018 by Gordon Kimball|work=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]]|publisher=Racer Media & Marketing, Inc.|first=Robin|last=Miller|authorlink=Robin Miller (journalist)|date=January 26, 2015|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref>

At 22, Kimball was diagnosed with type 1 diabetes and was forced to abandon his racing program midseason.<ref name="ABILITY magazine">{{cite news|title=Full Speed Ahead - Charlie Kimball runs laps around diabetes|url=http://www.abilitymagazine.com/charlie-kimball.html|accessdate=October 22, 2012|work=[[ABILITY Magazine]]|publisher=[[Chet Cooper]]}}</ref> Undeterred, he climbed back into the cockpit the following year and claimed a podium finish in his first race after returning.<ref name="ABILITY magazine" /> He is also the first licensed driver with diabetes in the history of IndyCar racing<ref name="ABILITY magazine" /> ([[Howdy Wilcox II|Howdy Wilcox]] hid the fact he was driving with diabetes in the 1932 Indy 500, but was barred from competing when officials found out before the 1933 race).<ref>Benbow, Dana. (May 23, 2015) [http://www.indystar.com/story/sports/2015/05/23/indycars-charlie-kimball-theres-no-gas-in-the-gas-tank/27602147/ IndyCar's Charlie Kimball: 'There's no gas in the gas tank'] ''The Indianapolis Star''. Retrieved May 22, 2016.</ref> [[Novo Nordisk]], the manufacturer of the insulin Kimball uses, became a full-time sponsor of his racing program in 2011.

Kimball married Kathleen, whom he first met in high school, in 2014, the wedding officiated by fellow driver [[James Hinchcliffe]].<ref>https://www.indianapolismonthly.com/the-thread/home-charlie-kathleen-kimball/</ref>  The couple relocated to Indianapolis, where they live with two dogs.<ref>https://www.indycar.com/News/2016/05/05-10-How-They-Met-Kimballs</ref>  Kathleen earned her MBA from [[Kelley School of Business|Indiana University Kelley School of Business]], and works at Kimball Marketing Group.<ref>https://www.linkedin.com/in/kathleen-kimball-2a58a93</ref>

Kimball is a long-time fan of the [[Los Angeles Dodgers]] baseball team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://old.seattletimes.com/html/sports/2020811677_apcarindycarblogdodgerskimball.html|title=Charlie Kimball awed by Dodgers experience|work=[[The Seattle Times]]|publisher=Frank A. Blethen, The Seattle Times Company|first=Jenna|last=Fryer|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=April 18, 2013|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref>

