{{use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox sportsperson | name = Schalk Booysen | birth_name = | image = | caption = | nationality = South African | sport = Sprinting | event = 200 metres | club = | collegeteam = | birth_date = {{birth date|1927|8|22|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Pretoria]], South Africa | death_date = {{death date and age|2011|5|1|1927|8|22|df=yes}} | death_place = | height = | weight = }}
'''Schalk Booysen''' (22 August 1927 &ndash; 1 May 2011) was a South African [[sprint (running)|sprinter]]. He competed in the [[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics – Men's 200 metres|men's 200 metres]] at the [[1952 Summer Olympics]]. He finished seventh in the [[1950 British Empire Games]] 880 yards. In the 1950 British Empire Games 440 yards he was eliminated in the heats.<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/schalk-booysen-1.html |title=Schalk Booysen Olympic Results |accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>
